# Amur, Altai Republic

}}
Amur (; , AmÄ±r) is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative centre of Amurskoye Rural Settlement, Ust-Koksinsky District, the Altai Republic, Russia. The population was 763 as of 2016. There are 11 streets.
Geography
Amur is located 47&nbsp;km northwest of Ust-Koksa (the district's administrative centre) by road. Abay is the nearest rural locality.
